# VS Code REST Client examples for Artha Actions
# Use the "REST Client" extension. Click "Send Request" on each block.
# Replace placeholder values in the variables section before running.
#
# Workflow covered:
# 1) Health check
# 2) Initiate deal (create on-chain intent)
# 3) Fund deal (payer signs and sends tx)
# 4) Mark delivered (seller submits evidence)
# 5) Release funds (buyer approves)  OR  Refund (fallback)
#
# Notes
# - The Actions server returns a ready-to-sign transaction payload.
# - You sign and submit with your wallet or a test helper.
# - Keep amounts tiny on devnet.

########################################
# Variables (edit these)
########################################
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8787
@apiKey =                         # optional: if your server requires it
@buyer =  BuyerWalletPublicKeyHere
@seller = SellerWalletPublicKeyHere
@mint  =  USDC                     # logical currency; your server decides mapping
@amount = 1.00                     # human amount; server converts to base units
@deliveryBy = 2025-11-30T23:59:59Z # ISO 8601
@disputeHours = 48
@dealId = D-REPLACE-ME             # will be returned by initiate; paste it below

########################################
### 1) Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

########################################
### 2) Initiate a deal
# Creates an escrow intent. Server should return:
#   - dealId (string)
#   - tx or blinkUrl for funding (optional convenience)
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/initiate
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "title": "Test escrow: used gadget",
  "buyer": "{{buyer}}",
  "seller": "{{seller}}",
  "amount": {{amount}},
  "mint": "{{mint}}",
  "deliveryBy": "{{deliveryBy}}",
  "disputeWindowHours": {{disputeHours}}
}

# After sending:
# - Copy the returned dealId into @dealId above.
# - If the response includes a blinkUrl or a serialized transaction,
#   open it with your wallet to fund in the next step.

########################################
### 3) Fund the deal
# If your UI used a Blink from the previous step, you can skip this and
# jump straight to step 6 to fetch the status.
# Otherwise, ask the server to build a funding tx for the payer.
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/fund
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "dealId": "{{dealId}}",
  "payer": "{{buyer}}"
}

# Response is a ready-to-sign transaction or a blinkUrl.
# Sign and submit with your wallet, then keep the signature for logs.

########################################
### 4) Mark delivered (seller provides evidence)
# Attach a CID if you already uploaded artifacts to IPFS or Arweave.
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/deliver
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "dealId": "{{dealId}}",
  "evidenceCid": "bafyREPLACE",
  "note": "Shipped via devnet courier"
}

########################################
### 5A) Release funds to seller (buyer approves)
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/release
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "dealId": "{{dealId}}",
  "approver": "{{buyer}}"
}

########################################
### 5B) Refund to buyer (alternate path)
# Use this only if delivery failed or a dispute resolved in buyer's favor.
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/refund
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "dealId": "{{dealId}}",
  "approver": "{{seller}}"
}

########################################
### 6) Fetch deal status
GET {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/{{dealId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

########################################
### 7) Open a dispute (optional)
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/dispute
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "dealId": "{{dealId}}",
  "reason": "Item arrived damaged",
  "evidenceCid": "bafyREPLACE-DISPUTE"
}

########################################
### 8) Resolve via ticket (arbiter or jobs-service suggestion)
# This endpoint is optional depending on your server design.
# Provide a signed ResolveTicket if your flow uses AI or human arbitration.
POST {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals/resolve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "dealId": "{{dealId}}",
  "ticket": {
    "schema": "escrow.v1.ResolveTicket",
    "deal_id": "{{dealId}}",
    "action": "RELEASE",
    "split_bps": 0,
    "rationale_cid": "bafyREPLACE-RATIONALE",
    "confidence": 0.9,
    "nonce": 1,
    "expires_at": 2000000000,
    "signature": "hex-encoded-sig",
    "public_key": "hex-encoded-pk"
  }
}

########################################
### 9) List recent deals (debug helper, if implemented)
GET {{baseUrl}}/actions/deals?limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
